          MODULE=kdeconnect-kde
         VERSION=26.04.2
          SOURCE=$MODULE-$VERSION.tar.xz
      SOURCE_URL=$KDE_URL/stable/release-service/$VERSION/src/
      SOURCE_VFY=sha256:45a197a2f2e7e400e6cf42f351cf92ca06807f1023f17378f128a3314c7fc176
        WEB_SITE=https://community.kde.org/KDEConnect
         ENTERED=20180305
         UPDATED=20260604
           SHORT="Communicate across all your devices"

cat << EOF
KDE Connect is a project to communicate across all your devices.
For example, with KDE Connect you can receive your phone notifications on your
desktop computer, control music playing on your phone from your desktop, or use
your phone as a remote control for your desktop.
To achieve this, KDE Connect:
  Implements a secure communication protocol over the network, and allows any
  developer to create plugins on top of it.
  Has a component that you install on your desktop
  Has a KDE Connect client app you run on your phone.
EOF
